-- в”Ђв”Ђ ElevenLabs в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$ElevenLabs is an AI audio research company that provides realistic text-to-speech, voice cloning, dubbing, and conversational voice agents through a web app and developer API.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (paid plans from $5/month billed annually, $6/month billed monthly)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2022, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$500-1,000+ employees (estimates vary by source; roughly 70 employees in 2023 growing to several hundred by 2025-2026)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$New York City, New York, United States (additional offices in London, UK and Warsaw, Poland)$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$ElevenLabs Review 2026: AI Voice Pricing & Features$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$ElevenLabs in 2026: pricing tiers from Free to Enterprise, voice cloning, text-to-speech, dubbing, and conversational AI agents reviewed in depth.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$ElevenLabs is an artificial intelligence audio technology company best known for producing some of the most natural-sounding synthetic speech available on the market. Founded in 2022 by Piotr DД…bkowski, a former Google machine learning engineer, and Mati Staniszewski, a former Palantir deployment strategist, the company was started after the two Polish-born founders noticed how poor the dubbing was on foreign-language films and set out to build AI models that could generate expressive, human-like voices in any language. ElevenLabs is headquartered in New York City, with additional engineering and operations hubs in London and Warsaw. The company has grown extremely quickly: it raised a Series C in early 2025 and, by February 2026, closed a $500 million Series D that valued the business at roughly $11 billion, more than tripling its valuation within a year. Investors have included Andreessen Horowitz, ICONIQ Growth, and Sequoia, among others, and total disclosed funding sits in the hundreds of millions of dollars.

At its core, ElevenLabs sells access to proprietary deep-learning voice models through a browser-based Speech Studio and a REST API. The flagship capability is text-to-speech, where users type or paste text and select from a large library of stock AI voices or a cloned voice to generate natural, emotionally inflected audio in dozens of languages. The platform's Voice Cloning tools range from Instant Voice Cloning, which needs only a short audio sample, to Professional Voice Cloning, which trains a higher-fidelity model from a longer, cleaner recording. Beyond narration, ElevenLabs offers Speech-to-Text transcription, an AI Dubbing Studio that can translate and re-voice video content while preserving the original speaker's tone, a Sound Effects generator, a music generation tool, and Conversational AI, a framework for building low-latency voice agents that can be plugged into phone systems, customer support workflows, and applications via API and native SDKs.

ElevenLabs prices its products on a monthly credit system, where credits are consumed based on characters generated, minutes transcribed, or agent usage. The Free plan includes 10,000 credits per month with access to text-to-speech, speech-to-text, sound effects, voice design, and a limited number of Studio projects, but output is for non-commercial use only. The Starter plan is $6/month (or roughly $5/month billed annually) and unlocks instant voice cloning, a commercial license, and 30,000 monthly credits. Creator, at $22/month, adds professional voice cloning and 121,000 credits, and is the tier most solo creators, podcasters, and YouTubers land on. Pro costs $99/month for 600,000 credits and higher-fidelity 44.1kHz PCM audio via the API. Scale, at $299/month, adds team seats and multiple professional voice clones for 1.8 million credits, and Business, at $990/month, scales further to 6 million credits with low-latency options and up to ten workspace seats. An Enterprise tier offers custom credit volumes, dedicated support, HIPAA-ready Business Associate Agreements, custom SSO, and elevated concurrency for large media, gaming, and customer-service deployments.

ElevenLabs' primary users span several very different audiences: independent content creators and podcasters who need affordable narration and dubbing; publishers, audiobook producers, and news organizations localizing content into multiple languages; game studios and film/TV post-production teams needing character voices and ADR; and, increasingly, enterprise software teams building voice agents for call centers, IVR replacement, and in-app assistants through the Conversational AI product and API. Because the API is metered and developer-friendly, ElevenLabs has also become a common backend voice provider embedded inside other SaaS products, from video editors to customer support platforms.

Competitors in the AI voice space include Google Cloud Text-to-Speech and Amazon Polly for basic synthetic speech, Play.ht and Murf AI for creator-focused narration, Resemble AI and Descript's Overdub for voice cloning, and OpenAI's own audio models for conversational use cases. ElevenLabs differentiates primarily on perceived voice realism and expressiveness вЂ” independent listening tests and creator communities have repeatedly ranked its voices among the most natural-sounding available вЂ” as well as breadth: few competitors combine text-to-speech, voice cloning, dubbing, sound effects, music, and conversational agents in a single platform with one credit pool. Notable facts include ElevenLabs' rapid rise to a multibillion-dollar valuation in under three years, its role in several high-profile AI-generated-audio controversies that pushed the company to introduce voice-verification and misuse-detection safeguards, and its widely used free-tier API that many indie developers rely on for prototyping voice features before scaling to paid usage.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '800f1735-5876-4cb4-b6d8-d7bee24e7a9f';

