-- в”Ђв”Ђ EmailOctopus в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$EmailOctopus is a London-based email marketing platform offering affordable newsletter campaigns, automation, and landing pages, built as a low-cost alternative to larger email service providers.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (Pro from $9/month)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2014, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$10-15 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$London, England, United Kingdom$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$EmailOctopus Review 2026: Pricing & Features$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$EmailOctopus in 2026: pricing plans, automation features, and landing pages reviewed for this budget-friendly email marketing platform from London.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$EmailOctopus is an email marketing platform founded in 2014 in London, England, built specifically to offer a lower-cost alternative to larger email service providers like Mailchimp. The company has grown steadily as a lean, self-sustaining business rather than a venture-backed hypergrowth startup, and reports indicate it is run by a small team of roughly ten to fifteen people while serving a large customer base вЂ” over 50,000 customers who collectively send more than 19 billion emails a year through the platform. That combination of a small internal team and a very large customer base is a recurring talking point in coverage of the company, and it reflects a deliberate focus on keeping the product simple, self-serve, and inexpensive to operate rather than expanding into a large enterprise sales organization.

The platform's core function is standard email marketing: users import or grow a subscriber list, design campaigns using a drag-and-drop or HTML editor, and send newsletters, promotions, or automated sequences to segmented audiences. EmailOctopus layers in marketing automation for sequences like welcome series and drip campaigns, basic audience segmentation, subscriber list management with import/export tools, and landing page and signup form builders that let users grow a list without needing a separate website. Under the hood, EmailOctopus has historically used Amazon Simple Email Service (Amazon SES) as its sending infrastructure, which is part of how it has been able to keep its own pricing significantly lower than competitors that operate and price around their own proprietary sending infrastructure.

EmailOctopus prices itself around subscriber-count tiers rather than email-volume tiers, following the model most of the email marketing industry uses. The Free plan supports up to 2,500 subscribers and 10,000 emails sent per month, with EmailOctopus branding included on sent campaigns, statistics retained for only 30 days, one landing page and one signup form, and access limited to a single user. The paid Pro plan starts at $9 per month (billed annually; noted as roughly $8/month in some slightly older pricing snapshots) for a base tier of 500 subscribers with unlimited monthly sends, and the price automatically scales upward as a subscriber list grows, following EmailOctopus's stated 'AutoUpgrade' approach to billing. Pro unlocks full control over email design and branding removal, indefinite statistics retention, unlimited landing pages and signup forms, and support for multiple user accounts on one workspace. For very large senders, EmailOctopus offers custom Enterprise pricing for accounts exceeding roughly 500,000 subscribers. The company also extends a 20% lifetime discount on any paid plan to verified non-profit organizations.

EmailOctopus's target users are small businesses, solo creators, bloggers, and startups that are price-sensitive and want core email marketing functionality вЂ” campaigns, automation, segmentation, and landing pages вЂ” without paying for the more elaborate CRM, e-commerce, or multichannel features bundled into higher-priced platforms. Its most direct competitors are Mailchimp, the dominant incumbent in small-business email marketing; MailerLite, another budget-focused competitor with a similar audience; ConvertKit, which targets creators and course sellers specifically; and Brevo (formerly Sendinblue), which bundles email with SMS and CRM tools. EmailOctopus differentiates itself almost entirely on price, positioning its paid plans as 40 to 60 percent cheaper than mainstream alternatives at comparable subscriber counts, while intentionally keeping its feature set focused rather than trying to match the breadth of larger all-in-one marketing suites. This price-first positioning, combined with its small team and reliance on Amazon SES infrastructure, has let EmailOctopus sustain a profitable, self-funded business model in a market segment usually dominated by heavily funded competitors.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'eb61be61-826d-402e-93f5-17aed2eb85a3';

