-- в”Ђв”Ђ Emplifi в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Emplifi is an enterprise customer experience platform combining social media marketing, social customer care, and social commerce tools, formed in 2021 from the merger of Socialbakers and Astute Solutions.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Custom / Quote-based$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$From $1,249/month (Social Marketing Essential); other products are custom-quoted$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2021, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$approximately 540-550 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Columbus, Ohio, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Emplifi Review 2026: Pricing & Features$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Emplifi in 2026: pricing tiers, social marketing, customer care, and commerce features reviewed for this enterprise customer experience platform.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Emplifi is an enterprise-grade customer experience platform focused on social media marketing, social customer care, and social commerce, used by large brands to manage how they market to, support, and sell to customers across social and digital channels. The company in its current form was created in June 2021 through the rebranding and combination of two previously separate businesses: Astute Solutions, a customer engagement software company originally founded in 1995, and Socialbakers, a well-known social media analytics and marketing platform. Astute Solutions acquired Socialbakers in September 2020, and roughly nine months later the combined organization relaunched under the single Emplifi brand, unifying the marketing-analytics strength of Socialbakers with the customer-care and CRM heritage of Astute into one product suite. Emplifi is headquartered in Columbus, Ohio, and operates internationally with employees across North America, Europe, and Asia; estimates place its current headcount at roughly 540 to 550 employees as of 2026, and the company has raised institutional backing from investors including Sixth Street, LionTree, Golub Capital BDC, and Audax Private Equity, with the business valued at roughly $1 billion.

Emplifi organizes its product suite into three connected pillars. Social Marketing covers social media publishing, scheduling, content calendaring, competitive benchmarking, and analytics across platforms like Instagram, Facebook, TikTok, and X, helping marketing teams plan and measure campaigns at scale. Social Care focuses on customer service delivered through social and messaging channels, giving support teams a unified inbox, automation, and AI-assisted response tools to manage high volumes of customer inquiries across platforms. Social Commerce connects social content and customer interactions to on-site shopping experiences, including ratings and reviews management and tools designed to turn social engagement directly into purchases. Across all three pillars, Emplifi has increasingly positioned itself around what it calls 'Autonomous Customer Experience,' layering AI-driven automation and predictive analytics on top of its existing tools to reduce manual work for large marketing, care, and commerce teams; some of the most advanced, predictive AI capabilities in its Social Care and Social Commerce 'Intelligent' tiers were, as of the most recent product roadmap, described as not yet generally available and slated for later rollout.

Emplifi's pricing is structured around named tiers within each of its three product pillars: Essential, Advanced, and Intelligent. For Social Marketing, published starting prices show Essential from roughly $1,249 per month for teams beginning to unify their social channels, and Advanced from roughly $2,499 per month for mid-sized teams needing deeper collaboration tools, while the top Intelligent tier is available only via a custom quote for large enterprises with complex, multi-brand operations. Social Care and Social Commerce tiers are priced entirely on a custom-quote basis rather than published rates, reflecting the more variable, deployment-specific nature of customer service and commerce integrations. Across all tiers and products, Emplifi states that pricing scales with business outcomes rather than seat count, and that plans include unlimited user licenses and unlimited owned social profile connections, a notable departure from the common industry practice of charging per user seat.

Emplifi's target customers are mid-market and enterprise brands, typically consumer-facing companies with substantial social media presence and customer service volume, that need to coordinate marketing, support, and commerce activities across multiple social and digital channels from a single platform, often across many regional or product-line social accounts simultaneously. Its competitors include Sprinklr and Hootsuite for enterprise social media management, Sprout Social for mid-market social marketing and engagement, and Khoros and Salesforce Social Studio for social customer care specifically. Emplifi differentiates itself by combining marketing, care, and commerce in a single connected suite rather than requiring separate tools for each function, by its unlimited-seat pricing philosophy, and by its ongoing investment in AI-driven, predictive customer-experience automation branded as Autonomous Customer Experience, which industry analyst Gartner recognized by naming Emplifi a Leader in the social customer experience space in 2026.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '8e87fe27-ae20-4a92-8b43-5f6016f6f4fa';

